bio: A compassionate therapist with over 10 years of experience in individual and group therapy. Specializes in stress management and life transitions.
Specializes in helping clients with anxiety, depression, and trauma. Uses an integrative approach tailored to individual needs.
Dedicated to supporting individuals and families through challenging times. Focuses on building resilience and coping skills.
Experienced in working with diverse populations, offering support for career stress, relationship issues, and personal growth.
Passionate about helping couples and individuals improve communication and foster healthier relationships.
Helps individuals navigate grief, loss, and life transitions with compassion and empathy.
Specializes in mindfulness-based approaches for stress reduction and emotional regulation.
Focuses on family systems and improving communication within relationships.
Provides support for young adults dealing with identity, career, and relationship challenges.
Experienced in treating OCD, phobias, and panic disorder using evidence-based techniques.
